  <brief_title>Active Symptom Control Alone Or In Combination With Oral Topotecan In Patients With Relapsed Resistant Small Cell Lung Cancer</brief_title>
  <official_title>An Open-Label, Multicentre, Randomised, Phase III Comparator Study of Active Symptom Control Alone or in Combination With Oral Topotecan in Patients With Relapsed Resistant SCLC</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>GlaxoSmithKline</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>GlaxoSmithKline</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to find out if giving oral HYCAMTIN to patients with relapsed
      small cell lung cancer benefits them. The study will compare how long patients live when they
      are given therapy to make them feel better (active symptom control) to the length of time
      patients live when they are also receiving oral HYCAMTIN.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
